	<tr>
		<td colspan="2"><hr class="sep" />I would like to mod my NES so it can accept famicom carts.
<br />I believe this should be relatively simple, but I am probably missing something since hardware is hardly my forte.  Could someone let me know if this is destined to fail?
<br />
<br />- scavenge a famicom connector off a famiclone
<br />- run wires from either the nes connector the board directly to the correspinding famicom connector pins
<br />- disable lockout chip
<br />
<br />Thanks for any help!

		

		</td>
	</tr>
